album.title: Now That's What I Call Music! Vol. 76

wiki.summary: "Midnight Sky" is a disco-influenced pop single from Miley Cyrus and the lead single off her 7th Studio album ‘’Plastic Hearts”. The song was the best-selling song of 2020 by a female in the United Kingdom. It was released on 14 August 2020 after being previously teased by the singer on 5 August 2020 when she began posting clips of the track on social media. The track places half-way through the album as track # 7 and samples Stevie Nicks’ “Edge Of Seventeen”. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Midnight Sky" is a disco-influenced pop single from Miley Cyrus and the lead single off her 7th Studio album ‘’Plastic Hearts”. The song was the best-selling song of 2020 by a female in the United Kingdom. It was released on 14 August 2020 after being previously teased by the singer on 5 August 2020 when she began posting clips of the track on social media. The track places half-way through the album as track # 7 and samples Stevie Nicks’ “Edge Of Seventeen”. There’s also a remix of the song titled “Edge Of Midnight” included in Cyrus’ album featuring Nicks. Read more on Last.fm.
